&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;We are looking for an exceptionally talented&lt;strong&gt; Director, Communication &amp;amp; Media Planning, &lt;/strong&gt;to oversee Media Planning and Strategy functions for any assigned clients. This person will lead a team in the development, execution, and stewardship of integrated media plans for the client’s business. The Director is a leader who contributes to brand strategy, builds solid relationships with clients across all levels and functions, and can manage, lead, and develop their internal strategy team while also playing an active “hands-on” role in the deployment of strategic plans.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Reporting to the VP, Head of Strategic Planning, you will be the lead architect of insight-led media strategies that turn complex data into compelling narratives. You will partner closely with Client Solutions to ensure our current NAM portfolio is thriving, while playing a pivotal leadership role in the business development process. Your superpower? Building the &quot;bridge.&quot; You’ll translate client business problems into actionable briefs and high-impact pitch decks that win new business. From guiding the &quot;big-idea&quot; brainstorms to ensuring Kip (Kepler Intelligence Platform) is leveraged for maximum strategic advantage, you will be the guardian of the &quot;red thread&quot; that connects a brand’s promise to its media performance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;f

&lt;p&gt;Kepler executes engineered marketing, where every message and ad delivered helps create a more personalized and productive relationship between brands and their consumers. We do this by acting as clients’ agency of record, as their in-house team, or some hybrid of the two – and by harnessing data and technology across all paid digital media and data-driven CRM channels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kepler prides itself on being a great place to work. In fact, we’re proud to share that AdAge recognized Kepler among the Best Places to Work in 2022, and Digiday named Kepler the Most Innovative Media Agency in 2025, validating our investment in our team and our clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We&#39;re transparent with our employees. You&#39;ll hear updates on company financials, how we&#39;re performing against bonus goals, and how we&#39;re responding to challenges we face.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We&#39;re growing. For you, that means unparalleled growth opportunities and a role in shaping the direction of the company.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We&#39;re fun. You&#39;ll work with and learn from the smartest people in the industry and have a blast doing it.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;The Role:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kepler is seeking a dynamic and data-driven Director of Data Strategy &amp;amp; Analytics for B2B to spearhead our initiatives across a portfolio of B2B marketing clients. This role requires a leader with a deep understanding of the paid media ecosystem, exceptional data acumen, and the ability to translate complex analytics and insights into strategic opportunities. The successful candidate will lead a talented team, driving innovation and excellence in data analytics to enhance media program optimization, develop a consultative partnership with clients, and establish actionable measurement roadmaps across accounts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The DS&amp;amp;A Director plays a critical role in ensuring client and company success. The position requires strong quantitative aptitude, experience with data-forward client management, business acumen to understand and advanced client marketing goals, and a desire to be part of a tightly-knit team that’s out to change the industry.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the senior analytics and data leader for a portfolio of brands, focused on B2B marketing, that will require hands-on client management, and exceptional communication and prioritizations skills.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain relationships with senior client stakeholders across marketing and analytics teams, and act as a point of escalation on all data and analytics matters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with internal and external stakeholders to determine business goals and analytics opportunities, developing comprehensive B2B measurement strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize your natural curiosity and drive to innovate to advance client-specific measurement programs and create new solutions to apply across clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex analytics and data into clear, cohesive insights for senior clients, and guide your team on how to do the same.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide the evolution of Kepler’s internal technology platform, Kip, establishing a feedback loop of client needs and applied learnings from new tools that set the development roadmap for our engineering team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspire, coach, and mentor staff across multiple disciplines, and shape Kepler culture through your leadership.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the trusted expert internally. Leverage your experience and knowledge to shape the department’s approach to B2B analytics and assist Kepler in driving new business grow

